List of heads of missions from the United Kingdom
[ edit ] Heads of Missions to non-sovereign territories
[ edit ] Heads of Missions to international organisations
This is a list of current heads of United Kingdom Missions abroad. It is up to date as of 9 April 2008 to the High Commissioner to Cameroon.

The United Kingdom does not maintain a full embassy or High Commission in a number of countries. In each of these cases, the heads of Missions to another country, usually a neighbouring one, is concurrently accredited to the other country. In most cases, a smaller, local mission provides for emergencies, and is headed up by a lesser diplomat or a member of the local British community.
List of heads of missions from the United Kingdom
In the case of the C te d'Ivoire , the embassy has been vacated for security reasons, although, in normal circumstances, a separate ambassadorial position would be maintained.
